reasoning: Leiomyosarcoma represents ~10-15% of soft tissue sarcomas. Global STS incidence ~4 per 100k; leiomyosarcoma ~0.4 per 100k. Second most common adult STS.
source: Toro JR et al. (2006). Incidence patterns of soft tissue sarcomas in the SEER program, 1978-2001. Int J Cancer. 119(12):2922-30
